'''''Money Madness''''' is a 1980 video game published by [[Instant Software]] for the [[TRS-80]].

==Contents==
''Money Madness'' is a game package containing two programs, ''Millionaire'' and ''Timber Baron''.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
Bruce Campbell reviewed ''Money Madness'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 39.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Campbell |first=Bruce |date=May 1981 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=39|pages=35}}</ref> Campbell commented that "For those interested in a business simulation, I recommend this package. Many single programs cost more. While ''Timber Baron'' is of primary interest, you may also enjoy a few games of ''Millionaire''."<ref name="SG"/>

